# Tech Stack

---

## Frontend

- Use plain HTML5 for page structure.
- Use CSS3 for styling, no preprocessors.
- Use vanilla JavaScript for interactivity, no frameworks.
- Use Leaflet for the Local Map feature, version 1.9.4, from https://leafletjs.com/.

---

## Backend

- Use Node.js with Express for the server.
- Use SQLite for the database, stored in `hospitality.db`.
- Use `express` for routing and API handling.
- Use `sqlite3` to connect to SQLite.
- Use `ws` for WebSocket chat.
- Use `node-fetch` to call the Cloudbeds API.
- Use `dotenv` for environment variables like API keys.

---

## APIs

- Use Cloudbeds API for guest data, from https://hotels.cloudbeds.com/api/docs/.
- Use OpenStreetMap with Leaflet for maps, from https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/.